Jayson has experience in venture capital, technology, sales, and marketing.
Prior to Rittenhouse, Jayson served as the President and Managing Director of the Wharton Social Venture Fund, a student-run organization that discovers, evaluates, and secures early-stage investments in key social sectors.
In his previous roles, Jayson has routinely advised promising technology startups on advanced marketing and sales strategies. Besides a sector focus in healthcare, he has a passion for education technology customer engagement solutions.
 
