Professional

                                    Prior                


PNC Equity Management Corp.


                  Incline Equity Partners focuses on investments in middle-market buyout and growth opportunities, targeting transactions of $20 million to $125 million. The firm typically serves as a lead investor and generally invests $10 million to $30 million per transaction. For larger investments, the often form investment syndicates.Incline Equity Partners seeks to invest in companies with proven business models and proven management teams. They focus on investments in niche manufacturing companies, outsourced services organizations and value-added distribution businesses. The firm prefers to invest in companies with significant market share that are operating in industries with attractive growth opportunities. Incline Equity Partners employs a flexible approach to structuring investments that considers future financing needs. They may take minority or a majority ownership positions in their portfolio companies.                




