Executive Profile
Bruce H. Luehrs  Founder and Managing Director, Delaware Valley CapitalAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 8 Board Members in 8 different organizations across 11 different industries.See Board Relationships63--
Background

		Mr. Bruce H. Luehrs serves as a Founder, Managing Partner and Partner at Rittenhouse Ventures, LLC (a/k/a Emerald Stage2 Ventures). Mr. Luehrs is a Co-Founder and Managing Partner of Penn Valley Group Investment Services. He is the Founder and Managing Director of Delaware Valley Capital. Mr. Luehrs is well known in the Philadelphia area and has an extensive background in venture capital, leveraged buyouts, equity and debt financings and investment banking for 30 years. ... Over eight years, he has championed investments in 14 companies totaling over $60 million. Mr. Luehrs' experience covers a wide range of industries including technology, media and telecom, financial services and consumer products. Prior to establishing Delaware in 2007, he was the Co-Founder and Managing Partner of the Penn Valley Group and focused on investment activities. Mr. Luehrs successfully led the management buyout of Smooth Fitness and made investments in Red Lasso and Health and Wellness Network. He was a General Partner of Edison Ventures Fund from 1998 to 2006, where he participated in investing over $250 million. During his tenure at Edison, Mr. Luehrs focused on investment opportunities in the telecommunications services, financial services information technology and pharmaceutical information technology sectors. He carried forward a lot of Edison investments in the Mid-Atlantic region including Gain Capital. Mr. Luehrs also carried forward investments in Virtual Edge, Fiberlink, Innaphase, Octagon and Cadient. Prior to Edison, He served as Vice President at Columbia Capital and a Principal at PNC Equity Management. While at PNC Equity Management, Mr. Luehrs directed its specialization on wireless telephone service investments. He was a commercial lender at Continental Illinois National Bank and Fidelity Bank. While at Fidelity, Mr. Luehrs developed a lending and investment practice serving emerging growth companies in the Delaware Valley and built a practice in funding leveraged buyouts. In 1988, Mr. Luehrs secured a SBIC license for Fidelity Bank and served as the President of the SBIC unit of Fidelcor Capital, where he began his investment activities as the Founder and the first President. He serves as Chairman of Miria Systems, Inc. Mr. Luehrs serves as a Director of Wellness Network and Business Intelligence International, Inc. He has been an Independent Director at Tabula Rasa Healthcare, Inc. since June 2014. Mr. Luehrs serves as a Director of TriSixty Security Inc. and Core Solutions, Inc. He serves as a Director of CoreStar Financial Group Inc., Business Intelligence International, Inc., Cadient Group, Inc. and Derivatives Portfolio Management. Mr. Luehrs serves as Board Observer of V-Span. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board at NextStage Capital, L.P. Mr. Luehrs served as a Director of FASTNET Corp. (AKA FN Estate, Inc.) since September 2001. He served as the Chairman of CorrectNet, Inc. Mr. Luehrs served as a Director of Fine Point Technologies, Inc., Octagon Research Solutions Inc. InnaPhase Corporation, Fiberlink Communications Corporation, GAIN Capital Group, LLC and Incurrent Solutions, Inc. He served as a Director of the Philadelphia Chapter of the National Association of Corporate Directors and active in the Association of Corporate Growth. Mr. Luehrs served as Chairman of the Greater Philadelphia Venture Group. He served as an Officer in the United States Air Force in 1975. Mr. Luehrs is a Member of the Association for Corporate Growth. He received an M.B.A. from the Kellogg School of Management at Northwestern University and graduated from Duke University with a B.A. in Economics, summa cum laude.Read Full Background




